 A group of armed bandits cold-bloodedly opened fire in the middle of public, while targeting a G4S transit vehicle, wounding three bystanders. The crowded garage was sent into a frenzied panic after a man refueling his vehicle was shot in his head, and a pregnant mother with her daughter were both wounded. Also read: Civilians shot in CIT heist It has been confirmed that the man died of his injuries, later in hospital. He has not yet been formally identified by his next of kin, but a murder docket has been opened. The two other victims have been identified as Ms Mariska Griffin and her daughter. The Griffins’ vehicle, where a stray bullet entered through the roof. They were both shot through the leg, but have since been discharged from hospital. The bullet went straight through the roof and was lodged into the panel framing the windscreen.       One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za